Key Match Events: Zac Gallen retired the next 12 batters in a row, striking out seven of them.
Heliot Ramos roped a one out double in the sixth, but Gallen got out of the jam easily by inducing a ground out and then striking out Matt Chapman for his final batter faced.
Post-Match Reflections: If the D-backs win their remaining three games against the Padres, then they are in the playoffs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zac Gallen struck out a season-high 11 batters in six dominant innings
Pavin Smith put the game on ice with a pinch-hit, three-run homer in the eighth, a moon shot into the pool.
